  <h2>Cooperative Mode</h2>

  <p>
    Buoy automatically detects existing AI code review tools and works <em>with</em> them
    instead of competing. When CodeRabbit, Greptile, or similar tools are detected,
    Buoy focuses on design system data and lets them handle AI review.
  </p>

  <pre><code># See what AI tools are detected
buoy lighthouse --detect-tools

# Export design system rules for CodeRabbit
buoy lighthouse --export-coderabbit

# Export context for Greptile
buoy lighthouse --export-greptile</code></pre>

  <h3>Supported Tools</h3>

  <ul>
    <li><strong>CodeRabbit</strong> — Export AST-based design system rules</li>
    <li><strong>Greptile</strong> — Export custom context for codebase understanding</li>
    <li><strong>Sourcery, Codacy, DeepSource</strong> — Detected, complementary (no export needed)</li>
  </ul>

  <p>
    Philosophy: Buoy provides design system expertise, AI tools provide code review.
    Together they're better than either alone.
  </p>

